  "title": "RecommendedResults break types when Server-side rendering in Remix/BFF",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nRemix JSONifies the API responses, which removes all `undefined` values from the objects.\r\n\r\nThe types for the SSR React InstantSearch expect the object to have the `params` key, but as it is marked as possibly `undefined` in the type, the JSONification marks this field as optional, and breaks the types.\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\nCheck the types in the `_index.tsx` file in the live CodeSandbox reproduction\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/algolia-type-issue-reproduction-fykfcr\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nTypes to match when rendering SSR\n\n### Package version\n\nalgoliasearch@4.24.0, instantsearch.js@4.73.2, react-instantsearch@7.12.2\n\n### Operating system\n\n_No response_\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
